reviews.review_text: Now this is the Grateful Dead that I fell in love with in concert! Unfortunately I only got to see them 8-10 times before Brent Mydland passed away & the sound changed quite a bit with Bruce Hornsby playing grand piano &/or  the accordion. I loved Bruce on the piano, the accordion, I could have gladly done without it. And Vince Welnick was really great on the keyboards, he just wasn't Brent. But from reading the notes this show was pieced together almost like a jigsaw  puzzle.n kit
